quran[175]{c,v,t}:
  39,32,"And who is a greater wrong-doer than he who fabricateth a lie against Allah, and belieth the truth when it cometh Unto him? Will not in Hell be an abode for the infidels"
  39,33,"And whosoever bringeth the truth, and whosoever giveth credence thereto - these! they are the God-fearing"
  39,34,"Theirs will be whatsoever they will desire with their Lord: that is the hire of the well-doers"
  39,35,"That through this Promise Allah may expiate from them the worst of that which they may have worked, and may recompense them their hire for the best of that which they have been working"
  39,36,"Is not Allah sufficient for His bondman? Yet they would frighten thee with those beside Him? And whomsoever Allah sendeth astray, for him there shall be no guide"
  39,37,"And whomsoever Allah guideth, for him there shall be no misleader. Is not Allah Mighty, and Lord of Retribution"
  39,38,"And wert thou to ask them: who hath created the heavens and the earth? they will surely say: Allah. Say thou: bethink ye then that those whom ye call upon beside Allah, - could they if Allah intended some hurt for me, remove His hurt? or if He intended some mercy for me, could they withhold His mercy? Say thou: enough for me is Allah; in Him the trusting put their trust"
  39,39,"Say thou: my nation! work according to your condition; I am going to work in my way; presently ye shall come to know"
  39,40,"On whom cometh a torment humiliating him, and on whom alighteth a torment lasting"
  39,41,"Verily We! We have sent down Unto thee the Book for mankind? with truth. Then whosoever receiveth guidance, it is for his soul and whosoever strayeth, strayeth only to its hurt; and thou art not over them a trustee"
  39,42,"Allah it is who taketh away souls at the time of their death, and those which die not in their sleep: then He withhold those on which He hath decreed death, and sendeth back the rest for an appointed term. Verily herein are signs for a people who ponder"
  39,43,"Have they taken others for intercessors beside Allah! Say thou: What! even though they own not aught and understand not"
  39,44,"Say thou: Allah's is intercession altogether. His is the dominion of the heavens and the earth; then Unto Him shall ye be returned"
  39,45,"And when Allah alone is mentioned, then shrink with eversion the hearts of those who believe not in the Hereafter, and when those beside Him are mentioned, lo! they rejoice"
  39,46,"Say thou: O Allah! Creator of the heavens and the earth! Knower of the hidden and the open! Thou shalt judge between Thy bondmen concerning that wherein they have been differing"
  39,47,"And were those who did wrong to own all that is in the earth, and there with as much again, they shall surely seek to ransom themselves therewith from the evil of the torment on the Day of Judgment; and there shall appear Unto them from Allah that whereon they had not been reckoning"
  39,48,"And there shall appear Unto them the evils that they earned, and there shall surround them that whereat they had been mocking"
  39,49,"When hurt toucheth a man he calleth on us, and thereafter, when We have changed it Unto a favour from Us, he saith: have been given itso only by force of my knowledge. Aye! it is a trial, but most of them know not"
  39,50,"Surely those who were before them said it, yet there availed them not that which they had been earning"
  39,51,And there befell them the evils of that which they had earned. And of these they who go wrong-anon will befall them the evils of that which they earn; nor can they frustrate
  39,52,"Know they not that Allahs expandeth provision for whomsoever He will, and stinteth it for whomsoever He will! Verily herein are signs for a people who believe"
  39,53,"Say thou: my bondmen who have committed extravagance against themselves despair not of the mercy of Allah; verily Allah will forgive the sins altogether. Verily He! He is the Forgiving, the Merciful"
  39,54,"And turn penitently Unto your Lord and submit Unto Him ere there cometh Unto you the torment, and then ye shall not be succoured"
  39,55,"And follow the best of that which hath been sent down Unto you from your Lord there cometh on you torment of a sudden, while ye perceive not"
  39,56,"Lest a soul should say: Alas! for that I have been remiss in respect of Allah, and I was but of the scoffers"
  39,57,"Or, lest it should say: had Allah but guided me, I should surely have been of the God-fearing"
  39,58,"Or lest it should say, when it will behold the torment: were there for me a return I would be of the well-doers"
  39,59,"Yea! surely there came Unto thee My revelations, but thou beliedest them and wast stiff-necked and wast of the infidels"
  39,60,And on the Day of Judgment thou Shalt see those who lied against Allah - their faces blackened. Is not in Hell the abode of the stiff-necked
  39,61,"And Allah will deliver those who feared Him to their place of safety. Evil will not touch them, nor will they grieve"
  39,62,"Allah is the Creator everything, And He is over everything a Trustee"
  39,63,His are the keys of the heavens and the earth and those who disbelieve in the revelations of Allah-those! they are the losers
  39,64,"Say thou: is it other than Allah that ye command me to worship! O ye pagans"
  39,65,"And assuredly it hath been revealed Unto thee and Unto those before thee: if thou associatest surely of non-effect shall be made thy work, and thou shalt surely be of the losers"
  39,66,"Aye! Allah must thou worship, and be among the thankful"
  39,67,"And they estimated not Allah with an estimation due Unto Him whereas the whole earth shall be His handful on the Day of Judgment, and the heavens shall be rolled in His right hand. Hallowed be He and Exalted above that which they associate"
  39,68,"And the trumpet will be blown, when whosoever are in the heavens and whosoever are on the earth will swoon away, save him whomsoever Allah willeth. Then it shall be blown again, and lo! They will be standing, looking on"
  39,69,"And the earth will gleam with the light of its Lord, and the Record shall be set up, and the prophets and the witnesses will be brought and judgment will be given between them with truth, and they will not be wronged"
  39,70,And each soul will be paid in full that which it hath worked; and He is the Best Knower of which they do
  39,71,"And those who disbelieve will be driven onto Hell in troops till, when they arrive thereto, the portals thereof will be opened, and the keepers thereof will say Unto them: came there not Unto you apostles from amongst you, rehearsing Unto you the revelations of you Lord and warning you of the meeting of this your Day? They shall say: Yea, but the word of torment hath been justified on the Infidels"
  39,72,"It will be said: enter the portals Of Hell to be abiders therein. How ill, then, is the abode of the stiff-necked"
  39,73,"And those who feared their Lord Will be driven Unto the Garden in troops till, when they arrive thereto, and the portals thereof will be opened, the keepers thereof Will say Unto them: Peace be Unto you! excellent are ye! enter it as abiders"
  39,74,"And they Will say: all praise Unto Allah, who hath fulfilled His promise Unto us and made us inherit this land, so that we may dwell in the Garden whereever we will! Excellent then is the hire of the workers"
  39,75,"And thou wilt see the angels thronging round the Throne, hallowing the praise of their Lord. And judgment shall be given between them with truth: and it will be said: all praise Unto Allah, the Lord of the worlds"
  40,1,Ha. Mim
  40,2,"The revelation of the Book is from Allah, the Mighty, the Knower. Forgiver of sin, and Accepter of repentance, severe in chastisement, Lord of power. There is no god but He; Unto Him is the journeying"
  40,3,"Forgiver of sin, and Acceptor of repentance severe in chastisement, Lord of Power. There is no god but He; unto Him is the journeying"
  40,4,"None dispute concerning the revelations of Allah save those who disbelieve, so let not beguile thee their going about in the cities"
  40,5,"The people of Nuh and the confederates after them belied their apostles before these, and each disbelieving community advanced toward their apostle that they may lay hold of him and disputed with vain speech that they may confute the truth thereby. Wherefore I laid hold of them; and how terrible was My chastisement"
  40,6,"And thus hath the Word of thy Lord been justified on those who disbelieve: that they shall be the fellows of the Fire"
  40,7,"Those who bear the Throne and those who are round about it, hallow the praise of their Lord and believe in Him and ask forgiveness for those who believe, saying: our Lord! Thou comprehendest everything in mercy and knowledge, wherefore forgive these who repent and follow Thine path, and protect them from the torment of the Flaming Fire"
  40,8,"Our Lord! make them enter the Everlasting Gardens Which Thou hast promised them, and also such of their fathers and their spouses and their offspring as verify Thou: Thou art the Mighty, the Wise"
  40,9,"And protect them from evils. And whosoever Thou shalt protect from evils on that Day, him Thou hast of a surety taken into mercy and that: it is an achievement mighty"
  40,10,"Verily those who disbelieve-they will be cried Unto: surely Allah's abhorrence was greater than Is your abhorrence toward yourselves when ye were called Unto the belief, and ye disbelieved"
  40,11,"They will say: our Lord! Thou hast made us die twice, and Thou hast made us live twice now We confess our sins: there no getting out any way"
  40,12,"That is because when Allah alone was called upon ye disbelieved, and when some one was associated with Him ye believed. So the judgment is of Allah, the Exalted, the Great"
  40,13,He it is who sheweth you His signs and sendeth down for you from the heaven provision. And none receiveth admonition save him who turneth in penitence
  40,14,"Wherefore call Unto Allah, making religion for Him pure, though the infidels be averse"
  40,15,"He is Lofty in degrees, Lord of the Throne. He casteth the spirit of His command upon whomsoever He will of His bondmen, that he may warn people of the Day of Meeting"
  40,16,"The Day whereon they will appear: naught of them will be concealed from Allah, Whose is the dominion to-day? It is of Allah, the One, the Subduer"
  40,17,To-day each soul will be recompensed for that which it hath earned; no wrong-doing to-day; verily Allah is Swift at reckoning
  40,18,"Wherefore warn them thou of the Day of portending, whereon the hearts will be in the throats, choking: then will be for the wrong- doers no ardent friend nor an intercessor to be given heed to"
  40,19,"He knoweth the fraudulence of the eyes, and that which the breasts conceal"
  40,20,"Allah decreeth with truth, while those whom they call upon beside Him cannot decree aught; verily Allah! He is the Hearer, the Beholder"
  40,21,"Have they not travelled about in the land so that they may behold of what wise hath been the end of those who were before them? They were mightier than these in strength and in the traces in the land. Yet Allah laid hold of them for their sins, and from Allah they had none as protector"
  40,22,"That was because their apostles were wont to bring them evidence, but they disbelieved; wherefore Allah laid hold of them. Verily He is strong, severe in chastisement"
  40,23,And assuredly We sent Musa with Our signs and a manifest authority
  40,24,"Unto Fir'awn and Haman and Qur'an, but they said: a magician, a liar"
  40,25,"And when he came to them with the truth from before Us, they said: slay the sons of those who have believed with him, and let their women live. And the plot of the infidels was naught but vain"
  40,26,"And Fir'awn said: let me alone, that may slay Musa, and let him call upon his Lord. Verily fear that he may change your religion or that he may cause to appear in the land corruption"
  40,27,"And Musa said: verily I seek refuge in my Lord and your Lord from every stiff-necked person who believeth not in a Day of Reckoning"
  40,28,"And a believing man of Fir'awn 's household, hiding his belief, said: would ye slay a man because he saith: my Lord is God, and hath come upto you with evidences from your Lord? If he is a liar, then upon him will be his lie, and if he is a truth-teller, then there will befall you some of that wherewith he threateneth you; verily God guideth not one who is an extravagant and a liar"
  40,29,"O My people! yours is the the dominion to-day: ye being overcomers in the land; but who will succour us aginst the scourge of God if it cometh Unto us! Fir'awn said: I shew you only that which see, and I guide you but to the path of rectitude"
  40,30,"And he who believed said: O my people. verily I fear for you a fate like the day of the confederates"
  40,31,"Like the wont of the people of Nuh and A'ad and Thamud and those after them, and God intendeth not any wrong Unto His bondmen"
  40,32,"And, O my people! verily fear for you a Day of Mutual Calling"
  40,33,"A Day whereon ye shall turn away retreating: for you there will be no protector from God; and whomsoever God sendeth astray for him there is no guide"
  40,34,"And assuredly there came Unto you Yusuf aforetime with evidences, yet ye ceased not to be in doubt concerning that which he brought Unto you, until when he died, ye said: God shall by no means raise an apostle after him. Thus Allah keepeth astray one who is extravagant and a doubter"
  40,35,"Those who wrangle concerning the signs of Allah without any authority that hath come Unto them. It is greatly abhorrent Unto Allah and Unto those who believe. Thus Allah sealeth up the heart of any stiff-necked, high-handed, person"
  40,36,"And Fir'awn said: O Haman! build for me a tower that haply I may reach the ways of access"
  40,37,"The way of access to the heavens so that may be apprised of the God of Musa, and verily I believe him to be a liar. And thus fair- seeming was made Unto FIr'awn the evil of his work, and he was hindered from the path. And the plot of Fir'awn ended only in ruin"
  40,38,"And he who believed said: O my people! follow me, I shall guide you to the path of rectitude"
  40,39,"O My people! this life of the world Is but a possi enjoyment, and verily the Hereafter! that is the Abode of rest"
  40,40,"Whosoever worketh an evil, he shallnotberequited except the like thereof; and whosoever, male or female, worketh righteously, and is a believer-they will enter the Garden wherein they will be pro vided for without measure"
  40,41,"And, O my people! what aileth me that call you Unto deliverance, while ye call me Unto the Fire"
  40,42,"Ye call me for this, that should O blaspheme against God and associate with Him that whereof have no knowledge, call you onto the Mighty, the"
  40,43,"Without doubt ye only call me Unto that which is not to be invoked in the world nor in the Hereafter; and verily our return shall be Unto God, and the extravagant! they shall be fellows of the Fire"
  40,44,And anon ye shall remember that which am telling you. Confide my affair Unto God; verily God is the Beholder of His bondmen
  40,45,"Wherefore Allah protected him from ills which they plotted, and there surrounded the family of Fir'awn the evil of torment"
  40,46,"The Fire! They are exposed thereto morning and evening. And on the Day whereon the Hour will uprise, it will be said: cause the family of Fir'awn to enter the most grievous torment"
  40,47,"And consider what time they will wrangle together in the Fire, and the oppressed will say Unto those who were stiff-necked: verily we have been Unto you a following, are ye going to avail us against a portion of the Fire"
  40,48,"Those who were stiff-necked will say: verily we are all in it; verily Allah hath judged between His bondmen"
  40,49,"And those in the Fire will say Unto the keepers of Hell: supplicate your Lord that He may lighten for us a day of the torment"
  40,50,"They will say: came there not your apostles Unto you with evidences? They will say: Yea? They will say: supplicate then yourselves. And supplication of the infidels will be but in wandering"
  40,51,"Verily We! We shall surely succour Our apostles and those who believe, both in the life of the world and on a Day whereon the witnesses will stand forth"
  40,52,A Day whereon their excuse will not Profit the wrong- doers; and theirs Will be the curse and theirs the evil Abode
  40,53,"And assuredly We vouchsafed Unto Musa the guidance, and We caused the Children of Isra'il to inherit the Book"
  40,54,A guidance and an admonition Unto the men of understanding
  40,55,"Wherefore persevere thou. Verily the Promise of Allah is true and ask forgiveness for thy fault, and hallow the praise of thy Lord in the evening and in the morning"
  40,56,"Verily those who wrangle concerning the revelations of Allah without an authority having come Unto them there is aught in their breasts save greatness Which they shall not reach. Seek refuge thou then in Allah verily He! He is the Hearer, the Beholder"
  40,57,The creation of the heavens and the earth is indeed greater than the creation of mankind; but most of man kind know not
  40,58,Not equal are the blind and the seeing; nor those who believed and Work righteous works and the evil-doer. Little are ye admonished
  40,59,"Verily the Hour is coming: there is no doubt thereof; yet most of mankind believe not"
  40,60,"And your Lord hath said: call Unto Me, and I shall answer your prayer. Verily those who are stiff-necked against My worship, anon they will enter Hell abject"
  40,61,"Allah it is who hath appointed for you the night that ye may repose therein, and day enlightening. Verily Allah is the Lord of Grace for mankind; bur most of mankind return not thanks"
  40,62,"Such is Allah. your Lord, the Creator of everything there is no God but He. Wither then are ye straying away"
  40,63,In this wise have those strayed who the signs of Allah were away want to gainsay
  40,64,"Allah it is Who hath appointed for you the earth for a resting-place and the heaven for a structure, and fashioned you and fashioned you well, and provided you with goodly things. Such is Allah, your Lord. So blessed be Allah, the Lord of the worlds"
  40,65,"He is the Living: there is no god but He so call upon Him, making religion pure for Him. All praise Unto Allah, the Lord of the worlds"
  40,66,"Say thou: verily I am forbidden that should worship these whom ye call upon beside Allah when evidences have come Unto me from my Lord, and I am commanded that I should submit to the Lord of the Worlds"
  40,67,"He it is Who created you of dust, and thereafter of a drop, and thereafter of a clot, and thereafter He bringeth you forth as an infant, and thereafter He ordaineth that ye attain your full strength and thereafter that ye become old men-though some of you die before-and that ye attain the appointed term, and that haply ye may reflect"
  40,68,"He it is Who causeth life and death. Then whensoever He decreeth an affair He only saith Unto it: be, and it becometh"
  40,69,"Observest thou not those who wrangle concerning the revelations of Allah: whither are they turning away"
  40,70,"Those who belie the Book and that message wherewith We sent Our apostles, presently they shall come to know"
  40,71,When shackles will be on their necks and also chains; they will be dragged
  40,72,Into the balling water; then into the Fire they will be stocked
  40,73,"Then it will be said Unto them: where are those whom ye have been associating"
  40,74,"Beside Allah? They will say: they have failed us: aye! we have not been calling upon aught afore. Thus doth Allah lead the infidels astray"
  40,75,"That is because ye had been exulting in the earth without right, and because ye had been strutting"
  40,76,Enter ye the gates of Hell as abiders therein. Hapless is the abode of the stiff-necked
  40,77,"Wherefore persevere thou; verily the promise of Allah is true; then whether We let thee see a part of that wherewith We have promised them, or whether We cause thee to die, Unto us they all will be caused to retvtn"
  40,78,"Assuredly We have sent apostlesy before thee, of them are these whose store We have recounted Unto thee and these whose story We have net recounted Unto thee. And it was not possible for anv apostle that he should bring a sign san by Allah's leave. So when the commade of Allah cometh, judgment will be given with truth, and then will lose the followers of falsehood"
  40,79,"Allah it is Who hath appointed for you cattle, that ye may ride on some of them, and eat of others"
  40,80,And there are other benefits in them for you and that ye may attain thereby to any need that is in Your breasts and upon them and upon ships ye are borne
  40,81,"And He sheweth you His signs. Which, then, of the signs of Allah shall ya deny"
  40,82,"Have they not travelled in the earth so that they may behold what wise hath been the end of those before them. They were more numerous than these, and mightier in strength and the traces in the land. But naught availed them of that which they had been earning"
  40,83,"And when their apostles came Unto them with evidences, they exulted in the knowledge which was with them, and there surrounded them that which they had been mocking"
  40,84,"Then when they behold Our prowess, they said: we believe in Allah alone, and we disbelieve in that which with Him we have been associating"
  40,85,But their belief profited them naught when they saw our prowess. This hath been Allah's dispensation that hath- been in regard to His bondmen. And then there were lost the infidels
  41,1,Ha-Mim
  41,2,"This is a revelation from the Compassionate, the Merciful"
  41,3,"A Book whereof the verses are detailed: an Arabic Qur'an: for a people who know"
  41,4,"A bearer of glad tidings and a warner. Yet most of them turn aside, so that they hearken not"
  41,5,"And they say: our hearts are under veils from that whereUnto thou callest us, and in our ears there is heaviness, and betwixt us and thee there is a curtain; work thou then, verily we are Workers"
  41,6,"Say thou: I am only a human being like Unto you: only it is revealed Unto me that your God is but One God, wherefore take the straight path Unto Him and seek forgiveness of Him. And woe be Unto the associators"
  41,7,"Who give not the poor-rate; and they! in the Hereafter, they are disbelievers"
  41,8,Verily those who believe and work righteous works - Unto them shall be a hire unceasing
  41,9,"Say thou: are ye indeed those who disbelieve in Him who hath created the earth in two days, and set up Unto Him peers? That is the Lord of the worlds"
  41,10,"And He placed therein mountains firmly rooted rising above it, and blessed it, and ordained therein the sustenance thereof, all this in four days: comglete: this for the inquirers"
  41,11,"Thereafter turned He to the heaven and it was as smoke, and said Unto it and Unto the earth: come ye twain, willingly or loth. They said: we come willingly"
  41,12,"Then He decreed them as seven heavens in two days, and revealed Unto each heaven the command thereof; and We bedecked the nether heaven with lamps and placed therein a guard. That is the ordinance of the Mighty, the Knower"
  41,13,"Then if they Still turn away, say thou; I warn you of a calamity like the calamity of the 'Aad and Thamud"
  41,14,"Recall what time the apostles came Unto them from before them and behind them, saying: worship none save Allah. They said: had our Lord listed, He surely would have sent down angels, so verily in that wherewith ye have been sent we are disbelievers altogether"
  41,15,"As for the tribe of 'Aad - they grew stiff-necked on the earth without justification, and said: who is mightier than we in strength? Saw they not that Allah who created them,-He was Mightier than they in strength? And Our signs they were wont to gainsay"
  41,16,"Wherefore We sent upon them a raging wind in days inauspicious, that We might make them taste the torment of humiliation in the life of the world; and surely the torment of the Hereafter will be more humiliating, nor will they be succoured"
  41,17,"And as for the tribe of the Thamud We guided them but they preferred blindness to the guidance, wherefore the bolt of the torment of abjection laid hold of them because of that which they had been earning"
  41,18,And We delivered those who believed and had been fearing
  41,19,And warn them of the Day whereon the enemies of Allah will be gathered Unto the Fire; and they will be set in bands
  41,20,"Until when they come to it, their ears and their sights and their skins will bear witness against them of that which they had been working"
  41,21,"And they will say Unto their skins: wherefore bear ye witness against us They will say: Allah hath caused us to speak, Who causeth everything to speak, and Who created you the first time and Unto whom ye are now caused to return"
  41,22,"Ye have not been taking cover against yourselves lest your ears and your eyes and your skins should bear witness against you, but ye imagined that Allah not much knew of that which ye were working"
  41,23,"That thought of yours which ye formed concerning Your Lord, hath ruined you, and ye have become of the losers"
  41,24,"Then if they are patient, the Fire is their home, and if they seek to please Allah, they will not be of those who are allowed to please Allah"
  41,25,And We have assigned Unto them some companions who made fairseeming Unto them that which was before them and that which was behind them justified upon them was the Word Pronounced on the communities of the jinn and mankind who passed away before them; verily they were the losers
  41,26,"And those who disbelieve say: hearken not Unto this Qur'an and babble therein, haply ye may overcome"
  41,27,"Wherefore We will surely cause those who disbelieve to taste a severe tor ment, and We will surely requite them the worst of that which they have been working"
  41,28,"That is the meed of the enemies of Allah: the Fire. Therein is their home of Abidence: a meed forasmuch as Our revelations they were wont to gainsay"
  41,29,"And those who disbelieve will say: our Lord! show us those, of the jinn and mankind, who led us astray and we will place them underneath our feet that they may be of the nithermost"
  41,30,"Verily those who say: our Lord is Allah, and have thereafter stood fast by it,- upon them there shall come down the angels: fear not, nor grieve, and rejoice in the tidings of the Garden which ye have been promised"
  41,31,"We are your friends in the life of the world and in the Hereafter; there in yours will be whatsoever your souls desire, and therein yours shall be whatsoever ye call for"
  41,32,"And entertainment from the Forgiving, the Merciful"
  41,33,"And who is better in speech than he who summoneth Unto Allah, and worketh righteously, and saith: verily I am one of the Muslims"
  41,34,"Nor can good and evil be equal. Repel thou evil with that which is goodly then behold he between whom and thee there was enmity, will be as though he was a warm friend"
  41,35,And none attaineth that except those who are patient; and none attaineth that except the owner of mighty good fortune
  41,36,"And if there inciteth thee an incitement from the Satan then seek refuge in Allah. Verily He! He is the Hearer, the Knower"
  41,37,"And of His signs are the night and the day and the sun and the moon. So prostrate not yourselves Unto the sun nor the moon. but prostrate yourselves Unto Allah who hath created them, if it is He alone whom ye are worshipping"
  41,38,"And if they grow stiff-necked, then verily those who are with thy Lord, hallow Him night and day, and they weary not"
  41,39,"And of His signs is that thou beholdest the earth lowly, and when We send down thereon water, it stirreth to life and groweth. Verily He who quickeneth is the Quickener of the dead. Verily He is over everything Potent"
  41,40,Verily those who blaspheme Our revelations are not hid from Us. Is he then who will be cast into the Fire better or he who cometh secure on the Day of Resurrection? Work whatsoever ye will; Verily He is of that which ye work the Beholder
  41,41,Verily those who disbelieve in the Admonition when it cometh Unto them are themselves to blame. Verily it is a Book mighty
  41,42,"Falsehood cannot come at it from before it or behind it It, a revelation from One Wise and Praiseworthy"
  41,43,Naught is said Unto thee save that which was said Unto the apostles afore thee. Verily thy Lord is Owner of forgiveness and Owner of afflictive chastisement
  41,44,"And had We made it a recital in a foreign tongue, they would have surely said: wherefore are the verses thereof not detailed? A foreign tongue and an Arab! Say thou: Unto those who have believed it is a guidance and a healing: and those who believe not, - in their ears there is a heaviness, and Unto them it is blindness. These are they who are cried Unto from a place far-off"
  41,45,"And assuredly We vouchsafed Unto Musa the Book, and difference arose concerning it; and had not a word gone forth from thy Lord, the affair would have been decreed between them. And verily they are in regard thereto in doubt and dubitating"
  41,46,"Whosoever worketh righteously it is for his soul, and whosoever worketh evil it is against it. And thine Lord is not an oppressor Unto His bondmen"